==English==

===Pronunciation===
* {{audio|en|En-au-put off.ogg|Audio (AU)}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|puts off|putting off|put off}}

# {{lb|en|transitive}} To [[procrastinate]].
#: {{ux|en|Don't '''put off''' your homework to the last minute.}}
#: {{ux|en|Don't '''put''' your homework '''off''' to the last minute.}}
#: {{ux|en|Don't '''put''' it '''off''' to the last minute.}}
#: {{ux|en|Don't '''put''' it '''off'''.}}
# {{lb|en|transitive}} To [[delay]] (a task, event, etc.).
#: {{ux|en|The storm '''put off''' the game by a week.}}
#: {{ux|en|The storm '''put''' the game '''off''' by a week.}}
#: {{ux|en|I'm too busy to see Mr Smith today. I'll have to '''put''' him '''off'''.}}
# {{lb|en|transitive}} To distract; to disturb the concentration of.
#: {{ux|en|Please be quiet. I'm trying to concentrate and you're '''putting''' me '''off'''.}}
# {{lb|en|transitive}} To cause to dislike; to [[discourage]] (from doing).
#: {{ux|en|Almost drowning '''put''' him '''off''' swimming.}}
# {{lb|en|transitive|archaic}} To [[take off]] (something worn).
#: {{ux|en|to '''put off''' a mask}}

====Usage notes====
* The object in all senses can come before or after the particle, except that personal pronouns nearly always precede the particle.

